```

The function `Z_DOMOBJ_P` is a macro that calls `php_dom_obj_from_obj(Z_OBJ_P((zv)))`. If `zv` is not an object or is uninitialized, this can result in undefined behavior or a crash.

**Root Cause:**  
If `iterator->curobj` is not of type `IS_OBJECT`, then `Z_OBJ_P(&iterator->curobj)` will be invalid, leading to a crash. There is no type check before this macro is used.

**Fix:**  
Add a type check before calling `Z_DOMOBJ_P(&iterator->curobj)`. Only call it if `Z_TYPE(iterator->curobj) == IS_OBJECT`.

**Patch:**
```diff
--- a/ext/dom/dom_iterators.c
+++ b/ext/dom/dom_iterators.c
@@ -192,8 +192,13 @@
-	intern = Z_DOMOBJ_P(&iterator->curobj);
-
-	if (intern != NULL && intern->ptr != NULL) {
+	intern = NULL;
+	if (Z_TYPE(iterator->curobj) == IS_OBJECT) {
+		intern = Z_DOMOBJ_P(&iterator->curobj);
+	}
+
+	if (intern != NULL && intern->ptr != NULL) {
```

